question.text: Which of the following is not correctly matched?

options.text: Basic oxides <math><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></math>

Neutral oxides <math><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">B</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></math>

Amphoteric oxides <math><mi mathvariant="normal">Z</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">S</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math>

solution.text: <math><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> is an acidic oxide, CO is neutral and BeO is an amphoteric oxide.
